  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Ideally, the generated queries should recover the original query from the forward phase.",
    "The set of recovered questions is then embedded by a language model and compared with the original question, producing a final score that determines whether the generated answer suffers from hallucination.",
    "We assume a source domain of textual queries and a target domain of textual answers.",
    "A fewshot prompt foot_0 (Brown et al., 2020), a corresponding query Q and a LLM denoted by F LLM, are provided.",
    "The query is constructed on top of the prompt and fed into the LLM to generate an answer to the query."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "A fewshot prompt foot_0 (Brown et al., 2020), a corresponding query Q and a LLM denoted by F LLM, are provided."
  ]
}